  "description": "<p>Stay warm when the mercury drops and then drops some more, the Guides Down Parka is a portable furnace that seals in heat. Water-resistant insulation blends down and synthetic in key places to offer compressible warmth that retains heat when it's damp. The outer shell is tough and water-resistant, great for dry, cold, squeaky-snow conditions.</p><ul><li>2-layer waterproof breathable VarioShell fabric protects you from slush and snow</li><li>650-fill power duck down provides pillowy insulation</li><li>Down insulation is Responsible Down Certified, so you can feel good about your down</li><li>Synthetic insulation stitched into underarms</li><li>Hook and loop cuff closure</li><li>Large, zippered chest pocket holds essentials</li><li>Insulated hood has a soft faux fur trim that diffuses harsh winter winds and zips off when you do not need it</li><li>Smooth lining glides over other fabric for easy layering</li></ul>",
